                            London, Melbourne, Toronto: Heinemann Ltd. (The Poetry Bookshelf), corr. ed.,
1969. xxx + 144 pp. £0.65.

Textual note, xiii; chronology, xv-xvi; selected bibliography, xvii-xviii; introduction,
xix-xxix; Sketches, 1-22; Island, 24-43; ARO, 44; 
NNR, 45-46; Songs, 47-59, 134-48; Thel, 60-65; 
MHH, 66-80; FR, 81-95; VDA, 111-20; Am,
121-33; Urizen, 149-64; SoL, 165-69; MSS., 23, 43, 97-110, 170-71, 180-84,
264-302; M (shorter text), 186-263; GoP, 303; designs for “To Tirzah” and
M (half-title for Bk. II and Milton’s track). Erdman text, with only occasional insertion
of commas or periods. Introduction places a critical commentary in context of Blake’s life and times;
excellent observations on the privacy of Blake’s notebook invectives. Generous but not intrusive
footnotes.

